#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:1
msgid "Version control integration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:3
msgid ""
"Use [pre-commit](https://pre-commit.com/). Once you [have it installed]"
"(https://pre-commit.com/#install), add this to the `.pre-commit-config.yaml` "
"in your repository:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:7
msgid ""
"repos:\n"
"  # Using this mirror lets us use mypyc-compiled black, which is about 2x "
"faster\n"
"  - repo: https://github.com/psf/black-pre-commit-mirror\n"
"    rev: 26.5.1\n"
"    hooks:\n"
"      - id: black\n"
"        # It is recommended to specify the latest version of Python\n"
"        # supported by your project here, or alternatively use\n"
"        # pre-commit's default_language_version, see\n"
"        # https://pre-commit.com/#top_level-default_language_version\n"
"        language_version: python3.11\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:21
msgid ""
"Feel free to switch out the `rev` value to a different version of Black."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:23
msgid ""
"Note if you'd like to use a specific commit in `rev`, you'll need to swap "
"the repo specified from the mirror to https://github.com/psf/black. We "
"discourage the use of branches or other mutable refs since the hook [won't "
"auto update as you may expect][pre-commit-mutable-rev]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:28
msgid "Jupyter Notebooks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:30
msgid ""
"There is an alternate hook `black-jupyter` that expands the targets of "
"`black` to include Jupyter Notebooks. To use this hook, simply replace the "
"hook's `id: black` with `id: black-jupyter` in the `.pre-commit-config.yaml`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:34
msgid ""
"repos:\n"
"  - repo: https://github.com/psf/black-pre-commit-mirror\n"
"    rev: 26.5.1\n"
"    hooks:\n"
"      - id: black-jupyter\n"
"        language_version: python3.11\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:44
msgid "The `black-jupyter` hook became available in version 21.8b0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:47
msgid ""
"See the [Jupyter Notebooks guide](../guides/"
"using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md) for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:50
msgid "Excluding files with pre-commit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:52
msgid ""
"When using pre-commit, there's an important distinction in how file "
"exclusions work. Pre-commit passes files directly to Black via the command "
"line, rather than letting Black discover files recursively. This means "
"Black's `--exclude` option won't work as expected because it only applies to "
"files discovered during recursive directory traversal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:58
msgid "To exclude files when using pre-commit, you have two options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:60
msgid "Option 1: Use pre-commit's exclude (Recommended)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:62
msgid "Configure exclusions directly in `.pre-commit-config.yaml`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:64
msgid ""
"repos:\n"
"  - repo: https://github.com/psf/black-pre-commit-mirror\n"
"    rev: 26.5.1\n"
"    hooks:\n"
"      - id: black\n"
"        exclude: ^migrations/|^generated/\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:73
msgid ""
"This is the recommended approach because pre-commit filters files before "
"passing them to Black, avoiding unnecessary processing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:76
msgid "Option 2: Use Black's force-exclude in pyproject.toml"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:78
msgid ""
"Black's `force-exclude` configuration option excludes files even when they "
"are passed explicitly as command-line arguments (which is how pre-commit "
"invokes Black). Simply add the pattern to your `pyproject.toml`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:82
msgid ""
"[tool.black]\n"
"force-exclude = '''\n"
"(\n"
"  ^migrations/\n"
"  | ^generated/\n"
")\n"
"'''\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:92
msgid ""
"Black automatically reads this configuration—no additional CLI arguments are "
"needed in your `.pre-commit-config.yaml`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/source_version_control.md:96
msgid ""
"The `force-exclude` option was added in version 20.8b0 specifically to "
"support workflows where files are passed directly via CLI, such as pre-"
"commit hooks and editor plugins."
msgstr ""
